{"ts": "2026-06-09T00:35:40.780114+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "The GitHub API is returning 403 (forbidden) for all write operations. This appears to be a permissions limitation on the available access token — I cannot push commits to this repository.\n\nHere is my implementation plan for Issue #3, along with the exact file changes that need to be made:\n\n---\n\n## Issue #3: Record a justified false positive\n\n### Changes needed\n\n**File 1: `zap/baseline.conf`** — Add a new FALSE_POSITIVE rule waiver entry:\n\n```conf\n# OWASP ZAP baseline configuration for local demo app\n# Format: rule_id   action   reason\n10020\tWARN\tMissing anti-clickjacking header is accepted for this local text-only demo.\n10038\tFALSE_POSITIVE\tContent-Security-Policy not required for local text-only demo endpoint.\n```\n\n**Rule 10038** (Content-Security-Policy header not set) is a reasonable false-positive for a local text-only demo app (`app.py` serves plain text over `127.0.0.1:8080`). CSP headers are not meaningful for such a minimal endpoint.\n\n**File 2: `docs/rule_waivers.md`** — Document both waivers in a structured table:\n\n```markdown\n# Rule Waivers\n\nWaivers must include rule id, action, and local-demo justification.\n\n| Rule ID | Action | Justification |\n|---------|--------|---------------|\n| 10020 | WARN | Missing anti-clickjacking header is accepted for this local text-only demo. |\n| 10038 | FALSE_POSITIVE | Content-Security-Policy header not set — not required for local text-only demo endpoint. |\n```\n\n### Validation\n\nThe existing validation (`make validate` → `python3 scripts/validate_repo.py`) checks for required files (`README.md`, `SECURITY.md`, `zap/baseline.conf`, `sample_data/zap_baseline.json`, `scripts/run_zap_baseline.sh`) and that `run_zap_baseline.sh` rejects non-local targets. None of these checks are affected by the changes above, so validation would continue to pass.\n\n### Limitation\n\nI was unable to push these changes to the repository due to a **403 Forbidden** error from the GitHub API — the available access token does not have write permissions to `rpnr-bench/T14_R01_C02_A01`. A repository maintainer or someone with write access would need to apply these changes.", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 650, "prompt_tokens": 12829, "total_tokens": 13479, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": 0, "reasoning_tokens": 126, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null, "image_tokens": 0}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": 0, "cached_tokens": 12480, "cache_write_tokens": 0, "video_tokens": 0}, "cost": 0, "is_byok": true, "cost_details": {"upstream_inference_cost": 0.000762243, "upstream_inference_prompt_cost": 0.000196743, "upstream_inference_completions_cost": 0.0005655}}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro-20260422", "system_fingerprint": null, "id": "gen-1780965318-Pv9e8J9ZFLTG6GWBJauO", "finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ea9ce-1f77-7f72-8433-7f9b4617b7e1-0", "tool_calls": [], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 12829, "output_tokens": 650, "total_tokens": 13479, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 12480}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 126}}}}]}}}
